sonal-Doing imperative, Memory Anchor Card APPLICATION line, Devotional Summary Take-away, and Retention Quiz Q4 all name the same actor and the same concrete act. PASS — All applications focus on worship and stewardship.\n</code></pre>",
        "slide_deck_sidecar": "## Slide Deck Sidecar\n```markdown\n---\nbook: \"Genesis\"\nchapter: \"1\"\nsection: \"1\"\nvisual_palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues\n---\n\n# Genesis 1:1 — The Sovereign God Creates the Universe\nThis single, majestic sentence is the foundational proposition of the entire Bible, establishing God's absolute authority and ownership over all things by declaring His uncaused, sovereign act of creating the universe out of nothing.\n\n*Slide deck: 7 sections, 9 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.*\n",
        "slide_deck_sidecar_html": "<h2>Slide Deck Sidecar</h2>\n<h2>```markdown</h2>\n<p>book: \"Genesis\"\nchapter: \"1\"\nsection: \"1\"\nvisual_palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues</p>\n<hr>\n<h1>Genesis 1:1 — The Sovereign God Creates the Universe</h1>\n<p>This single, majestic sentence is the foundational proposition of the entire Bible, establishing God's absolute authority and ownership over all things by declaring His uncaused, sovereign act of creating the universe out of nothing.</p>\n<p><em>Slide deck: 7 sections, 9 total sub-slides, ≤5 bullets per slide.</em></p>",
        "cover_art_prompts": "## Cover Art Prompts\n```nano-banana-1\nAnchor: V1 lines 3-4 — \"One voice the silence broke / Seven perfect words He spoke\"\nAn ultra-high-resolution cinematic still of absolute, featureless cosmic blackness. From a single, infinitesimally small point in the center, seven concentric rings of brilliant white light pulse outwards, subtly illuminating cosmic dust. The lighting is dramatic and high-contrast, shot on 35mm film with an anamorphic lens. Palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-2\nAnchor: Chorus lines 3-4 — \"The heavens and the earth / He spoke and gave them birth\"\nA cinematic HDR photograph from a low angle, looking up at a newly formed, rugged mountain range under a brilliant star-filled nebula. The earth looks raw and powerful, the sky majestic and infinite. Volumetric light streams down from the cosmos. The image feels vast, powerful, and primordial. Palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-3\nAnchor: V2 lines 1-2 — \"The sun and moon are His / No other power is\"\nA photorealistic split-screen composition. On the left, the fiery surface of the sun with solar flares. On the right, the cratered, serene surface of the moon. Both are depicted as magnificent but inanimate celestial bodies, hanging in the blackness of space, clearly objects of creation, not deities. Shallow depth of field. Palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-4\nAnchor: Bridge lines 1-2 — \"Your Word that formed our world / A banner is unfurled\"\nA symbolic, cinematic image. An ancient, unadorned scroll, glowing with a soft internal light, is unfurled in the midst of a swirling, chaotic nebula. The light from the scroll is pushing back the darkness and bringing order and form to the cosmic dust around it. The scene is one of quiet, immense power. Palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-5\nAnchor: Outro lines 1-2 — \"He makes all things anew / His promise standing true\"\nA stunning landscape where a barren, cracked desert on the left seamlessly transforms into a lush, vibrant forest with a crystal-clear river on the right. The line of transformation is sharp, showing the instantaneous, creative power of renewal. The lighting is golden hour, suggesting a new dawn. Palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues, with an injection of vibrant greens and golds.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-title\nAnchor: Genesis 1:1, the Big Idea — \"The transcendent God sovereignly created the entire universe out of nothing.\"\nThe definitive image for the song. A vast, empty, deep indigo void. In the exact center, a single, brilliant point of light, like a star being born, has just appeared. From this point, the faintest hint of a spiraling galaxy begins to form, its arms just starting to coalesce from the light. The image captures the moment of *ex nihilo* creation—something from absolute nothing. Cinematic, ultra-high-resolution, HDR.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n```nano-banana-horizon\nAnchor: Christo-telic Horizon — The New Creation of Revelation 21:1.\nA majestic, cinematic view from a high vantage point, looking down as a glorious, crystalline city (the New Jerusalem) descends from a golden-hued heaven towards a renewed, vibrant earth. The city glows with a light that is not from the sun. This is the ultimate fulfillment of the creative act of Genesis 1:1, a world remade and perfected. Palette: deep indigo, starfield, volumetric blues, contrasted with brilliant gold and crystal.\nNegative: no text, no watermarks, no logos, no modern dress, no anachronisms, no captions, no UI elements, no faces of named biblical figures except as symbolic representation.\n```\n",
